{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019R8ig1aGpDuW3TqyzEYEV8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n**Resources deployed:**\n- `crdb-cluster` — headless Service (ClusterIP: None) for pod DNS, exposing grpc/26257 and http/8080\n- `crdb-cluster-public` — regular ClusterIP Service for client access\n- `crdb-cluster` StatefulSet — 3 replicas, `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, insecure mode, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` (required so all 3 pods start simultaneously and can join each other)\n- 3× PVCs `datadir-crdb-cluster-{0,1,2}` — 10Gi each, all Bound\n- `crdb-cluster-pdb` PodDisruptionBudget — `minAvailable: 2` ensures quorum is preserved during voluntary disruptions\n\n**Key fix:** The StatefulSet uses `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` instead of the default `OrderedReady`. With `OrderedReady`, pod 0 must become Ready before pods 1 and 2 are created — but pod 0 waits to join them, creating a deadlock. `Parallel` starts all 3 simultaneously, then a single `cockroach init` bootstraps the cluster.\n\nAll 3 nodes report `is_available: true` and `is_live: true`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1109,"cache_read_input_tokens":38734,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1109},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa8dfa00-9fbc-42f4-a31b-33f620dd9bcd","uuid":"f4014fc3-cdd1-4ff6-a078-f35666b3fe5e","request_id":"req_011CcfdTywZ4VzLArAcsfTVW"}
